  "plan": "# Restaurant Booking System Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Backend (.NET 10 Web API)\n\n### 1.1 Project Setup\n- Create solution structure: `RestaurantBooking.Api` + `RestaurantBooking.Domain` + `RestaurantBooking.Tests`\n- Add NuGet packages: FluentAssertions, Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi\n- Configure `TreatWarningsAsErrors` and strict mode\n\n### 1.2 Domain Layer (Pure functions, Result-style errors)\n- **Entities**: `Restaurant`, `Table`, `Booking`\n- **Value Objects**: `TimeSlot`, `PartySize`\n- **Errors**: `BookingError` (union type): `RestaurantNotFound`, `TableNotFound`, `InvalidPartySize`, `InvalidDateTime`, `SlotNotAvailable`, `OverlappingReservation`\n- **Domain Services**: `BookingService` with pure `CreateBooking()` and `GetAvailableSlots()` functions returning `Result<T, BookingError>`\n\n### 1.3 Infrastructure (In-memory persistence)\n- `InMemoryRestaurantRepository`, `InMemoryBookingRepository`\n- No EF Core needed for eval scope\n\n### 1.4 API Layer\n- `RestaurantsController`: `GET /api/restaurants`, `GET /api/restaurants/{id}/tables`\n- `BookingsController`: `POST /api/bookings`, `GET /api/bookings?restaurantId=&date=`\n- `AvailabilityController`: `GET /api/restaurants/{id}/availability?date=&partySize=`\n- OpenAPI/Swagger enabled with descriptive document for client generation\n- Thin controller shells calling domain services\n\n### 1.5 Tests (Boundary tests)\n- `BookingServiceTests`: conflict prevention, invalid party size, invalid times, overlapping reservations\n- All tests run without rebuild\n\n## Phase 2: Frontend (React SPA + Vite)\n\n### 2.1 Project Setup\n- Vite + React + TypeScript\n- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components\n- TanStack Query + TanStack Router\n- Orval for OpenAPI client generation from backend swagger endpoint\n\n### 2.2 Scripts\n```json\n{\n  \"build\": \"orval --config orval.config.ts && vite build\",\n  \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n  \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n  \"format:check\": \"prettier --check .\",\n  \"deadcode\": \"tsci --noEmit\"\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 Features (Vertical Slices)\n\n**Restaurant List Slice**\n- `GET /api/restaurants` via generated client\n- TanStack Query hook `useRestaurants()`\n- Card-based list with shadcn UI\n\n**Availability Slice**\n- Restaurant selection → party size + date picker\n- `GET /api/restaurants/{id}/availability` via generated client\n- Displays available time slots\n\n**Booking Form Slice**\n- Selected restaurant, table, time slot, guest details\n- TanStack Query mutation `useCreateBooking()`\n- Zod validation on form\n\n**Bookings View Slice**\n- `GET /api/bookings` filtered by restaurant/date\n- TanStack Query hook `useBookings()`\n- Confirmation display\n\n### 2.4 UI Polish\n- shadcn: Card, Button, Input, Select, Form, Toast\n- Responsive grid layout\n- Accessible form labels and error messages\n- Loading skeletons via TanStack Query `isLoading` states\n\n## Phase 3: Integration & Verification\n\n### 3.1 Backend\n- `dotnet build` passes with warnings as errors\n- `dotnet test` passes (including boundary tests)\n- `dotnet format --verify-no-changes` passes\n\n### 3.2 Frontend\n- `npm install` succeeds\n- `npm run build` (includes Orval generation) succeeds\n- `npm run typecheck` passes\n- `npm run lint` passes\n- `npm run format:check` passes\n- `npm run deadcode` passes\n\n### 3.3 README\n- Run instructions: `dotnet run` for API, `npm run dev` for frontend\n- Prerequisites: .NET 10 SDK, Node 18+\n- Ports: API on 5000, frontend dev on 5173\n\n## Implementation Order\n1. Domain (errors, entities, services) + tests\n2. API controllers + in-memory repo\n3. Backend verification (build, test, format)\n4. Frontend scaffolding + Orval config\n5. Feature slices (restaurants → availability → booking → list)\n6. Frontend verification (all scripts)\n7. README\n",
